The White House hosted a virtual Celebration of Afro-Latino Heritage as part of Black History Month programming. The event highlighted President Biden's commitment to equity and diversity in his administration. The program included two panels and remarks from Ambassador to Spain Julissa Reynoso, Senior Advisor Cedric Richmond, and Dean Pedro Noguera. There was also a spoken word performance by Melania Luisa Marte. The discussions focused on Afro-Latino representation and achieving Black wellness. Participants shared their experiences as leaders in the Afro-Latino community and administration officials discussed accomplishments from the first year of the Biden-Harris administration.